50|$|Leccinum versipelle, {{also known}} as Boletus testaceoscaber or the orange birch bolete, is a common edible {{mushroom}} (given the right preparation) in the genus Leccinum. It is found below birches from July through to November, and turns <b>black</b> when <b>cooked.</b>|$|R
5000|$|Bulgogi (불고기): {{thinly sliced}} or {{shredded}} beef marinated in soy sauce, sesame oil, garlic, sugar, green onions, and <b>black</b> pepper, <b>cooked</b> on a grill (sometimes at the table). Bulgogi literally means [...] "fire meat." [...] Variations include pork (dweji bulgogi), chicken (dak bulgogi), or squid (ojingeo bulgogi).|$|R
